news.title: Chandigarh housing board decides to expedite disposal of pending applications
news.para: "Now, it has been decided that all pending applications, which were filed before March 31, will be finalised in a mission mode," said Yashpal Garg, chief executive officer, CHB.

news.title: Nagpur: In third attempt too no bids for Patwardhan Ground project
news.para: The project to be built on PPP basis is part of MahaMetro’s initiatives to generate non-fare revenue through real estate leasing. The Patwardhan Ground complex is one of two such major projects.

news.title: Haryana Shehri Vikas Pradhikaran launches five apps to help allottees
news.para: The HSVP’s new app will unburden the allottees or users from the need to visit HSVP’s offices for getting the reallotment of unit in case of death, transfer due to sale or other reasons.

news.title: Ludhiana Improvement Trust to carry out Atal Apartment draw on June 16
news.para: The LIT had received good response for the HIG flats, whereas for MIG flats there was not much response. There are total 576 flats, out of those 336 are HIG while 240 are MIG flats.

news.title: Bengaluru: NGT puts halt to construction near Yele Mallappa Shetty lake
news.para: Jagan Kumar had filed an application with the NGT Southern Zone stating that the department has been constructing the pump house and that construction waste and debris were being dumped in the lake.

news.title: Chandigarh: Queries abound as property tax rebate deadline looms
news.para: The department concerned has been addressing public queries so that people deposit their property tax payment well in time to avail the rebate facility.

news.title: Building plan violators in Jamshedpur on JNAC radar
news.para: As per rule, only three-storied buildings can be constructed in the Tata Steel-subleased area, but most builders violate this rule and construct additional two to three floors without civic body’s permission.

news.title: I-T department issues lookout circular against GBP directors
news.para: According to sources, the LOC was issued against GBP directors Pardeep Kumar, Satish Kumar and Raman Kumar for not remitting the tax deducted at source (TDS) with the department to the tune of nearly Rs 30 crore, including penalties.

news.title: Rainwater harvesting must in Chandrapur, defaulters to face action
news.para: CMC commissioner Rajesh Mohite said Rs20,000 to Rs50,000 is taken as security deposit against developing rainwater harvesting facility in the building while approving the plan.

news.title: East Delhi civic body blames government staff for illegal buildings
news.para: “They are doing registry of flats/floors/houses without checking facts and working in connivance with building contractors,” said EDMC mayor Shyam Sunder Agarwal.

news.title: Sobha's net profit grows 39.66% in Q4 FY22
news.para: The company's total consolidated income stood at Rs 7,668 millions in Q4 FY22, a growth of 30.21 per cent from Rs 5,889 millions it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's net profit falls 33.13% to Rs 93.61 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: However, its total revenue from operation increased 3.34 per cent to Rs 620.03 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 599.95 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.

news.title: Chintels India seeks lifting of ban on registries of other projects
news.para: Chintels India, the developer, claimed to have paid a compensation of Rs 4.5 crore to the affected families and provided alternative accommodations to them.

news.title: SWAMIH fund invests over Rs 94 crore in Panvelkar Estate-Oxford near Mumbai
news.para: The fund has invested over Rs 94 crore in the project Panvelkar Estate-Oxford spread over 11 acres in Badlapur locality, said persons with direct knowledge of the development.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing Finance's net profit up 11% at Rs 307 crore
news.para: "The profit grew on the back of lower credit cost and higher profit from co-lending business and securitisation," its deputy managing director Ashwini Kumar Hooda said.
